1
00:00:00,084 --> 00:00:01,838
<i>Previously on</i> Breaking Bad...

2
00:00:02,211 --> 00:00:03,919
This whole Gale situation.

3
00:00:04,087 --> 00:00:05,379
It's just not working out.

4
00:00:05,547 --> 00:00:09,091
- What's up, partner?
- This is my replacement?

5
00:00:09,259 --> 00:00:11,969
I understand that you have a problem
with two of my employees.

6
00:00:12,137 --> 00:00:14,180
It is true that they killed
one of your associates.

7
00:00:14,348 --> 00:00:16,849
They got an 11-year-old kid
doing their killing for them.

8
00:00:17,017 --> 00:00:18,770
No more children. Understand?

9
00:00:19,562 --> 00:00:21,177
Grandma? Oh, God.

10
00:00:28,902 --> 00:00:29,694
Run.

11
00:01:12,676 --> 00:01:14,350
- Hello again.
- Hi!

12
00:01:14,475 --> 00:01:15,855
I hope we're not too late.

13
00:01:15,980 --> 00:01:17,325
No, no.
Perfect timing.

14
00:01:17,450 --> 00:01:18,959
Stan, this is my husband Walt.

15
00:01:19,084 --> 00:01:21,694
- Hi. Good to meet you, Walt.
- Nice to meet you.

16
00:01:21,819 --> 00:01:24,029
- Sandia Laboratories?
- Yeah.

17
00:01:24,154 --> 00:01:26,752
I hear some pretty fascinating
stuff goes on out there.

18
00:01:27,311 --> 00:01:28,701
You know...

19
00:01:28,826 --> 00:01:30,549
Working on anything
you can talk about?

20
00:01:30,674 --> 00:01:34,035
I'm picturing giant space lasers.
Am I right?

21
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:36,273
Honestly, what I do
would bore you senseless.

22
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:39,354
But giant space lasers?
Now, that sounds cool.

23
00:01:39,953 --> 00:01:41,948
I'll have to bring it up
at our next staff meeting.

24
00:01:42,073 --> 00:01:44,578
- Just remember I get a cut.
- All right, that's a deal.

25
00:01:45,219 --> 00:01:47,012
So this is it, honey.
What do you say?

26
00:01:47,647 --> 00:01:49,233
- Do you want to take a tour?
- Sure.

27
00:01:51,843 --> 00:01:54,297
Look, how about I give
y'all some privacy?

28
00:01:54,818 --> 00:01:57,322
I'll go out to the car
and make a few calls.

29
00:01:58,127 --> 00:01:59,859
Take as much time as you need.

30
00:01:59,984 --> 00:02:01,549
- All right. Good.
- Okay. Thanks.

31
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:07,073
He's actually a nice guy.
He doesn't push.

32
00:02:07,822 --> 00:02:10,766
So, as you can see, there's...

33
00:02:10,891 --> 00:02:12,669
there's a kind of flow
going on here.

34
00:02:12,794 --> 00:02:14,383
It's a nice big living room.

35
00:02:14,984 --> 00:02:18,290
And this is the dining area.

36
00:02:18,699 --> 00:02:20,674
- The dining area. Right.
- Yes.

37
00:02:21,073 --> 00:02:22,073
And...

38
00:02:23,746 --> 00:02:26,179
- It's got a pool.
- Oh, pool is nice.

39
00:02:28,238 --> 00:02:30,249
Backyard could be a little bigger.

40
00:02:31,150 --> 00:02:33,608
And...
there's a breakfast bar

41
00:02:33,733 --> 00:02:36,153
kind of dealie here which is nice.

42
00:02:36,278 --> 00:02:39,157
And, I don't know,
the kitchen's really spacious

43
00:02:39,282 --> 00:02:42,178
and, you know,
got good appliances, and...

44
00:02:42,485 --> 00:02:43,862
How many bedrooms?

45
00:02:44,581 --> 00:02:45,397
Three.

46
00:02:45,522 --> 00:02:46,398
Told you.

47
00:02:46,523 --> 00:02:48,261
There'll all pretty good size,
and...

48
00:02:48,386 --> 00:02:50,706
this is the first one here.

49
00:02:50,831 --> 00:02:53,153
And then there's
two more at the back.

50
00:02:53,278 --> 00:02:54,423
Only three bedrooms?

51
00:02:55,586 --> 00:02:58,441
I think we're gonna need at least five.
Don't you think?

52
00:02:58,566 --> 00:02:59,314
Five?

53
00:03:00,168 --> 00:03:01,202
What?

54
00:03:01,327 --> 00:03:04,413
Do I look like I'm about
to drop a litter? Dude.

55
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:07,597
No, we'll have three kids
total, eventually.

56
00:03:08,742 --> 00:03:11,237
But we'll need
a spare room for a study

57
00:03:11,362 --> 00:03:14,262
so that I could work at home
and you can write.

58
00:03:15,981 --> 00:03:16,898
I don't...

59
00:03:17,023 --> 00:03:18,650
I don't think this
is gonna be enough.

60
00:03:20,939 --> 00:03:21,865
Okay.

61
00:03:21,990 --> 00:03:23,431
What about a wine cellar?

62
00:03:23,974 --> 00:03:25,833
I mean, we certainly
cannot be expected

63
00:03:25,958 --> 00:03:27,654
to live without a wine cellar.

64
00:03:27,779 --> 00:03:28,994
Very funny.

65
00:03:29,119 --> 00:03:31,997
I just think we need to set
our sights high is all.

66
00:03:32,122 --> 00:03:33,574
At least higher than here.

67
00:03:34,905 --> 00:03:36,877
This is a good neighborhood.

68
00:03:37,281 --> 00:03:40,363
It's got a good elementary
and supposedly a very good high school.

69
00:03:40,488 --> 00:03:42,564
And believe me... 'cause I have

70
00:03:42,689 --> 00:03:45,254
definitely looked everywhere...

71
00:03:45,917 --> 00:03:48,376
for our price range,
this is as good as it gets.

72
00:03:48,501 --> 00:03:50,889
Then let's stretch our price range.

73
00:03:51,889 --> 00:03:53,634
Truly.
I mean, why

74
00:03:53,759 --> 00:03:57,377
why buy a starter house when we'll
have to move out in a year or two?

75
00:03:58,092 --> 00:03:59,965
Did you win the lottery
and not tell me?

76
00:04:00,619 --> 00:04:02,334
I'm serious.

77
00:04:02,736 --> 00:04:03,985
Come on.

78
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:06,137
Why be cautious?

79
00:04:06,262 --> 00:04:08,312
We've got nowhere to go but up.

80
00:04:12,836 --> 00:04:15,836
Subtitles:
Michvanilly, Tyno

