00:04:25,834 --> 00:04:28,184
www.sous-titres.eu
www.seriessub.com

82
00:06:23,569 --> 00:06:24,984
<i>Walter, you see us?</i>

83
00:06:25,939 --> 00:06:27,171
Yeah, I see you.

84
00:06:28,290 --> 00:06:29,852
<i>I'd like you to exit your vehicle</i>

85
00:06:29,977 --> 00:06:31,877
<i>and start walking toward us.</i>

86
00:06:32,788 --> 00:06:33,857
And then what?

87
00:06:34,404 --> 00:06:36,004
I'm gonna need some...

88
00:06:37,218 --> 00:06:38,868
some kind of assurance.

89
00:06:40,288 --> 00:06:43,200
<i>I assure you I could kill you
from way over here,</i>

90
00:06:43,325 --> 00:06:45,475
<i>if it makes you feel any better.</i>

91
00:07:39,918 --> 00:07:40,959
Walter,

92
00:07:41,683 --> 00:07:43,033
you've been busy.

93
00:07:44,006 --> 00:07:47,171
You want to put your arms out
to the sides for me, if you would?

94
00:08:03,785 --> 00:08:06,319
You know I haven't slept
since Thursday?

95
00:08:06,739 --> 00:08:09,120
I was out all night
cleaning up after you.

96
00:08:09,974 --> 00:08:11,357
I need my sleep.

97
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:15,364
You said no half measures.

98
00:08:17,737 --> 00:08:20,418
Funny how words can be
so open to interpretation.

99
00:08:22,997 --> 00:08:24,774
You get your car fixed?

100
00:08:24,899 --> 00:08:25,923
Not yet.

101
00:08:26,214 --> 00:08:28,377
You're gonna want
to get your car fixed.

102
00:08:28,775 --> 00:08:30,569
Let's see how this goes first.

103
00:09:05,973 --> 00:09:07,765
Has your condition worsened?

104
00:09:08,785 --> 00:09:11,599
- Excuse me?
- Your medical condition,

105
00:09:11,724 --> 00:09:14,142
- has it grown worse?
- Not that I know of, no.

106
00:09:14,847 --> 00:09:16,947
Is there a ringing in your ears?

107
00:09:17,617 --> 00:09:19,975
Are you seeing bright lights
or hearing voices?

108
00:09:21,704 --> 00:09:22,994
I'm quite well, thank you.

109
00:09:24,181 --> 00:09:25,868
Clearly you are not.

110
00:09:26,295 --> 00:09:29,051
No rational person
would do as you have done.

111
00:09:30,765 --> 00:09:32,115
Explain yourself.

112
00:09:36,209 --> 00:09:38,777
My partner was about
to get himself shot.

113
00:09:39,801 --> 00:09:40,951
I intervened.

114
00:09:41,609 --> 00:09:43,786
Some worthless junkie...

115
00:09:44,411 --> 00:09:46,814
For him you intervene
and put us all at risk?

116
00:09:47,494 --> 00:09:50,567
Some contemptible junkie who couldn't
keep the peace for eight hours?

117
00:09:51,561 --> 00:09:53,411
That's right.
He couldn't.

118
00:09:54,054 --> 00:09:56,598
He was angry because
those two dealers of yours

119
00:09:56,723 --> 00:09:58,818
had just murdered
an 11-year-old boy.

120
00:09:59,182 --> 00:10:00,532
I heard about it.

121
00:10:01,262 --> 00:10:03,673
He should have let me
take care of them.

122
00:10:04,134 --> 00:10:05,134
Maybe.

123
00:10:06,237 --> 00:10:09,236
Then again, maybe he thought
it was you who gave the order.

124
00:10:12,737 --> 00:10:14,087
Are you asking me

125
00:10:15,044 --> 00:10:17,637
if I ordered the murder of a child?

126
00:10:20,415 --> 00:10:22,265
I would never ask you that.

127
00:10:28,756 --> 00:10:30,379
Where is Pinkman now?

128
00:10:32,625 --> 00:10:33,928
I wouldn't know.

129
00:10:35,455 --> 00:10:37,482
A couple of time zones
away, at least.

130
00:10:39,028 --> 00:10:41,085
Beyond that, I'd only be guessing.

131
00:10:42,058 --> 00:10:43,944
He has enough money to last forever.

132
00:10:44,069 --> 00:10:45,989
He knows he needs to keep moving.

133
00:10:46,842 --> 00:10:48,415
You'll never find him.

134
00:10:48,676 --> 00:10:50,073
I don't know, Walt.

135
00:10:51,236 --> 00:10:52,876
It's what I do, after all.

136
00:10:56,014 --> 00:10:57,640
He's out of the picture.

137
00:10:58,115 --> 00:11:00,059
I saved his life.
I owed him that.

138
00:11:00,473 --> 00:11:02,127
But now he and I are done,

139
00:11:02,252 --> 00:11:04,821
which is exactly what
you wanted, isn't it?

140
00:11:10,295 --> 00:11:13,572
You've always struck me
as a very pragmatic man,

141
00:11:13,697 --> 00:11:16,679
so if I may, I would like
to review options with you

142
00:11:17,458 --> 00:11:20,035
of which it seems
to me you have two.

143
00:11:21,505 --> 00:11:22,505
Option A...

144
00:11:23,707 --> 00:11:25,251
you kill me right here and now.

145
00:11:25,929 --> 00:11:28,054
Apparently, I have made
that very easy for you.

146
00:11:28,831 --> 00:11:30,671
You can kill me... no witnesses...

147
00:11:31,576 --> 00:11:34,798
and then spend the next
few weeks or months

148
00:11:35,668 --> 00:11:38,004
tracking down Jesse Pinkman,
and you kill him too.

149
00:11:38,904 --> 00:11:40,917
A pointless exercise,
it seems to me.

150
00:11:41,042 --> 00:11:42,592
But that is Option A.

151
00:11:43,205 --> 00:11:44,704
What is Option B?

152
00:11:44,829 --> 00:11:46,173
I continue cooking.

153
00:11:46,966 --> 00:11:48,978
You and I both forget about Pinkman.

154
00:11:49,630 --> 00:11:51,577
We forget this ever happened.

155
00:11:52,097 --> 00:11:54,580
We consider this a lone hiccup

156
00:11:55,078 --> 00:11:56,256
in an otherwise

157
00:11:56,730 --> 00:11:58,185
long and fruitful

158
00:11:58,310 --> 00:11:59,593
business arrangement.

159
00:12:01,513 --> 00:12:02,947
I prefer Option B.

160
00:12:10,323 --> 00:12:12,173
You'd need a new assistant.

161
00:12:13,725 --> 00:12:15,525
I could get right on that.

162
00:12:16,342 --> 00:12:17,842
This time, I choose.

163
00:12:34,648 --> 00:12:35,563
Your car.

164
00:12:36,624 --> 00:12:37,774
Get it fixed.

165
00:13:19,250 --> 00:13:20,095
Really?

166
00:13:48,934 --> 00:13:50,245
It's good to see you.

167
00:13:52,161 --> 00:13:52,935
Thanks.

168
00:13:55,091 --> 00:13:56,641
It's good to be back.

169
00:13:59,424 --> 00:14:01,279
- Shall we?
- By all means, Gale,

170
00:14:02,248 --> 00:14:03,298
let's cook.

171
00:14:11,972 --> 00:14:13,553
What about that rhinoceros?

172
00:14:13,678 --> 00:14:15,245
You think he'd make a good pet?

173
00:14:17,039 --> 00:14:19,608
Don't you think if you called to him,
he'd come running for his supper?

174
00:14:19,910 --> 00:14:22,145
I'll bet he would.
I bet he'd come running.

175
00:14:23,788 --> 00:14:25,165
You're silly, Pop Pop.

176
00:14:25,290 --> 00:14:26,533
Well, a little.

177
00:14:26,658 --> 00:14:28,335
But he'd probably
knock everything over.

178
00:14:28,460 --> 00:14:30,104
Plus, there's that big nose of his.

179
00:14:30,229 --> 00:14:32,506
That's not a nose.
That's a horn.

180
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:34,372
Is that so?

181
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:36,143
His real nose is little.

182
00:14:38,470 --> 00:14:40,616
I learn all kinds of
things being with you.

183
00:14:45,310 --> 00:14:47,249
Okay, June Bug, these are for you.

184
00:14:47,374 --> 00:14:49,656
- What about the rest?
- The rest are for me.

185
00:14:49,781 --> 00:14:52,426
No, they're not.
You're too old for balloons.

186
00:14:54,043 --> 00:14:55,730
You're never too old for balloons.

187
00:14:56,290 --> 00:14:58,019
Give me a hug.

188
00:14:58,144 --> 00:15:00,355
I see your mama.
Don't keep her waiting.

189
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:02,528
- Bye, Pop Pop.
- Bye, baby.

190
00:17:08,823 --> 00:17:10,623
Please. Please, no.

191
00:18:29,829 --> 00:18:32,485
Chow, do you have anything
you want to tell me?

192
00:18:32,653 --> 00:18:34,116
Thank God you're here.

193
00:18:34,241 --> 00:18:35,686
They keep me prisoner.

194
00:18:35,811 --> 00:18:37,021
They keep you prisoner.

195
00:18:37,146 --> 00:18:39,492
I don't do nothing for them ever.

196
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:41,452
They try and make me.

197
00:18:41,716 --> 00:18:42,659
I say no.

198
00:18:43,259 --> 00:18:44,867
They steal my chemicals.

199
00:18:44,992 --> 00:18:46,697
I can't stop them.

200
00:18:46,822 --> 00:18:48,965
- I am businessman.
- You're a businessman...

201
00:18:49,234 --> 00:18:50,734
The lady out front...

202
00:18:51,125 --> 00:18:53,047
Lady, are you still there?

203
00:18:53,215 --> 00:18:54,627
Ask her if she's still there.

204
00:19:09,544 --> 00:19:10,844
She says yes.

205
00:19:12,515 --> 00:19:13,610
How's her driving?

206
00:19:14,077 --> 00:19:15,827
Driving. Is she good
behind the wheel?

207
00:19:16,176 --> 00:19:18,263
Good. She's good driver.

208
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:21,199
Licensed? Dependable?

209
00:19:21,535 --> 00:19:22,869
She has a Camry.

210
00:19:23,786 --> 00:19:24,621
Good.

211
00:19:28,864 --> 00:19:31,610
The trucks will be here
first thing in the morning.

212
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:35,404
I strongly recommend that you
return our calls next time.

213
00:19:35,912 --> 00:19:38,051
So have her drive you
to the hospital.

214
00:19:42,376 --> 00:19:44,371
She's gonna need her shoe.

215
00:19:55,837 --> 00:19:57,033
Where did they cross?

216
00:19:57,158 --> 00:19:58,608
Laredo, looks like.

217
00:19:59,327 --> 00:20:01,432
They didn't exactly send
their A players.

218
00:20:02,225 --> 00:20:04,373
But like you said,
it's cartel, all right.

219
00:20:07,368 --> 00:20:08,657
Probing for weakness.

220
00:20:10,704 --> 00:20:12,194
Well, they didn't find any.

221
00:20:15,806 --> 00:20:17,256
What about Pinkman?

222
00:20:18,833 --> 00:20:20,440
I'm making inquiries.

223
00:20:37,403 --> 00:20:38,396
Done. That's two?

224
00:20:38,521 --> 00:20:40,521
All right.
Let's close it up.

225
00:20:48,979 --> 00:20:50,179
Bring it down.

226
00:20:51,493 --> 00:20:52,293
Ready?

227
00:20:57,790 --> 00:20:59,518
Okay. We're good.

228
00:21:05,551 --> 00:21:07,601
You can take your mask off now.

229
00:21:18,316 --> 00:21:19,928
Does that guy ever leave?

230
00:21:23,375 --> 00:21:25,275
When exactly did that start?

231
00:21:26,168 --> 00:21:27,411
It's new.

232
00:21:28,919 --> 00:21:29,969
We had a...

233
00:21:32,046 --> 00:21:35,146
We had a little drama
with the person you replaced.

234
00:21:36,401 --> 00:21:37,661
I'm sorry to hear that.

235
00:21:38,092 --> 00:21:39,444
No, it'll be fine.

236
00:21:39,569 --> 00:21:41,264
Things will continue to smooth out.

237
00:21:43,132 --> 00:21:44,632
Yeah, it'll be fine.

238
00:21:47,626 --> 00:21:48,676
By the way,

239
00:21:49,258 --> 00:21:52,403
if you're at all worried
about working with me...

240
00:21:52,528 --> 00:21:53,628
No, I'm not.

241
00:21:54,604 --> 00:21:56,443
Because whatever
my shortcomings last time,

242
00:21:56,568 --> 00:21:59,953
I intend for things to go
perfectly from here on out.

243
00:22:00,336 --> 00:22:01,806
So, if there is...

244
00:22:01,931 --> 00:22:03,514
Gale, you're great.

245
00:22:04,061 --> 00:22:05,061
Seriously.

246
00:22:05,499 --> 00:22:06,449
I just...

247
00:22:07,193 --> 00:22:09,384
However you like things to be done

248
00:22:09,509 --> 00:22:12,047
is exactly how we are gonna do them.

249
00:22:12,321 --> 00:22:13,171
Period.

250
00:22:14,694 --> 00:22:15,894
From here on out.

251
00:22:16,019 --> 00:22:16,811
So...

252
00:22:19,917 --> 00:22:21,217
please teach me.

253
00:22:28,122 --> 00:22:28,914
Okay.

254
00:23:51,936 --> 00:23:52,680
Gale.

255
00:23:53,127 --> 00:23:54,294
It's good to see you.

256
00:23:54,419 --> 00:23:55,419
Mr. Fring.

257
00:23:56,172 --> 00:23:56,894
Wow.

258
00:23:57,019 --> 00:23:59,046
- This is...
- I should have called first.

259
00:23:59,171 --> 00:24:01,070
I'm not interrupting anything, am I?

260
00:24:02,851 --> 00:24:04,832
No, not at all.
Please come in.

261
00:24:07,758 --> 00:24:09,771
Can I offer you something?
Crème de Menthe?

262
00:24:11,860 --> 00:24:12,784
No, thank you.

263
00:24:13,446 --> 00:24:15,596
I'm sorry for the inconvenience.

264
00:24:17,236 --> 00:24:18,946
